=============================================================================
Halide for HVX

Halide is a programming language that greatly simplifies the development of
vision applications for Hexagon Vector Extensions. For more information on
the Halide language, please refer to https://halide-lang.org.

=============================================================================

Top level directory description:


docs - contains the Halide user's guide and training documents

Examples - tests for building applications for simulation and on device

lib - contains the Halide runtime libraries for simulation and on device

include - various header files for compilation

tools - contains GenGen.cpp

bin - tool to asist in simulating Hexagon offload mode

support - header file for benchmark timing


Please see Examples/README for instructions on running example Halide programs for HVX.

Please refer to RELEASE_NOTES for changes since previous release.

